%F A036561 T(n,k) = A013620(n,k)/A007318(n,k). - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, May 14 2006
%F A036561 T(n,k) = T(n,k-1) + T(n-1,k-1) for n>=1 and 1<=k<=n with T(n,0) = 2^n for n>=0. - _Johannes W. Meijer_, Sep 22 2010
%F A036561 T(n,k) = 2^(k-1)*3^(n-1), n, k > 0 read by antidiagonals. - _Boris Putievskiy_, Jan 08 2013
%F A036561 a(n) = 2^(A004736(n)-1)*3^(A002260(n)-1), n > 0, or a(n) = 2^(j-1)*3^(i-1) n > 0, where i=n-t*(t+1)/2, j=(t*t+3*t+4)/2-n, t=floor[(-1+sqrt(8*n-7))/2]. - _Boris Putievskiy_, Jan 08 2013
%F A036561 G.f.: 1/((1-2x)(1-3yx)). - _Geoffrey Critzer_, Jun 23 2016
%F A036561 T(n,k) = (-1)^n * Sum_{q=0..n} (-1)^q * C(k+3*q, q) * C(n+2*q, n-q). - _Marko Riedel_, Jul 01 2024
